  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, after a few weeks, I contracted [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] typhoid fever.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then my good friend, [INAUDIBLE], who was also from my hometown, being a son of a doctor, recognized quicker than others.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he brought an expert who said that I have to be hospitalized in [NON-ENGLISH] Hospital in Vilna.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At that time, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my father, who was very worried about my health-- and he had something important to discuss with me according to the letter and phone call.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anyway, so he took the train on June 21st in the evening.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1941, to go to Vilna.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when he arrived, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the next morning [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there were bombs falling on the-- on the railroad station in Vilna and around it, and of course [INAUDIBLE] airport.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was the beginning of Barbarossa, the German attack on Poland-- on-- on Russia, on the 22nd of June.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In two days, the Russians run away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Soviet government disintegrated, was replaced by the Wehrmacht, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] whom the Lithuanians, ignorant of the fact that the Germans sold them out in 1939, regarded as their saviors.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I spent three very unpleasant weeks in hospital.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then I was told that around the-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the end of-- of June that I'm ready to be discharged.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I was also warned by the Polish nuns that Germans and Lithuanian activists are arresting Jews or shooting them on sight.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At that time I remembered by heart the phone number of Dainelis and correctly anticipated that he would be back in the service of the Lithuanian police.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I telephoned him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was very happy I was alive, asked me to stay where I am.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
